A registered person, who was engaged in the sale of taxable goods as well as exempted goods or tax-free goods under the existing law but which are liable to tax under this Act, shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, the amount of credit of value-added tax and entry tax, if any, carried forward in a return furnished under the previous law by him, and the amount of credit of value-added tax and entry tax, if any, in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock on the appointed day, relating to such exempted goods or tax-free goods in accordance with the provisions of the Act. The following registered taxable persons will be eligible for the Input Tax Credit:

Those who were not liable to be registered under the existing Law;

Those who were involved in the sale of exempted goods or tax-free goods;

Goods which have suffered tax at the first point of sale and their subsequent sale was not liable to tax in the Union Territory under the previous law but which are liable to be taxed in GST;

Persons entitled to the credit of input tax at the time of the sale of goods.

